# Coding standards

- TypeScript strict. No `any` (ESLint errors). Prefer precise types and discriminated
  unions over loose objects.
- Respect package boundaries and the dependency direction:
  `content → sim (types)`, `game → sim + content`, `render → sim + content`,
  `ui → game`, `app → all`. Never import `react`/`three`/DOM into `@grid/sim`.
- All external/content data is validated with Zod at the boundary, then trusted as a
  typed value internally. New content must conform to a schema in `@grid/content`.
- Keep modules small and single-purpose. Co-locate tests as `*.test.ts`.
- Comments explain intent and trade-offs, not what the code obviously does.
- Game logic is data-driven: adding a track, part, card, or cosmetic should be a data
  change validated by a schema, not an engine change.
